      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p> Castle Nugent National Historic Site Establishment Act of 2013 - Establishes the Castle Nugent National Historic Site on the island of St. Croix, U.S. Virgin Islands, as a unit of the National Park System in order to preserve, protect, and interpret a Caribbean cultural landscape spanning over 300 years of agricultural use, significant archeological resources, an extensive barrier coral reef system, and other outstanding natural features. </p> <p>Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to lease certain lands within the boundary of the Historic Site to the University of the Virgin Islands for the purpose of continuing the University's operations for breeding Senepol cattle. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2013-01-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2013-01-16T21:27:23Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
